[2
Date: Mon, 23 Apr 2001 10:22:09 -0400
From: Jolynn Pratt Montgomery <PrattJM@state.mi.us>

Is the quadravalent vaccine for _N. meningitidis_ (which includes
W135) widely available in the UK? Also, given the high rate of disease
in contacts of Haj pilgrams (2/3 of the case-patients), should broader
use of vaccine be considered, especially in Arab communities?
In response to the moderators comment, "one wonders whether compulsory
vaccination should be considered," it is my understanding that
vaccination is required. However, should vaccination with a vaccine
that contains W135 be compulsory for travel to the Haj?
--
JoLynn Pratt Montgomery, PhD, MPH
Communicable Disease Epidemiology Specialist
Michigan Department of Community Health
